description: Six children died and 14 were injured in a tragic school bus accident near Unhani village, Narnaul, Haryana, due to the driver's high speed. The students were from GL Public School in Kanina, Mahendragarh.
title: 6 kids killed, several injured after school bus overturns in Haryana

description: Rashid Khan's brilliant all-round performance led Gujarat Titans to victory in an intense Indian Premier League match against Rajasthan Royals in Jaipur on Monday. Rashid's match-winning boundary off the final ball of the game, along with Shubman Gill's half-century, secured the win for 2022 champions while chasing Rajasthan's 196 for 3.
title: Watch: Rashid Khan's 'special gesture' after GT's win vs RR

description: Apple to inform iPhone users in India and 91 other countries about sophisticated 'mercenary spyware' attacks like Pegasus. Users urged to take warnings seriously and follow protection tips on the updated support page.
title: Apple warns: India, 91 more nations 'mercenary spyware' attack

description: A woman who authorities say fatally stabbed her partner at their Los Angeles apartment Monday then threw her two children from a moving SUV onto the freeway, killing her infant daughter, was an astrologer who called the impending solar eclipse “the epitome of spiritual warfare” in an online post days earlier.
title: US astrology influencer allegedly kills partner, baby amid solar eclipse concerns

description: Rajasthan Royals skipper Sanju Samson has been fined Rs 12 lakh for his team's slow over rate in a thrilling IPL match against Gujarat Titans. The Titans, led by Shubman Gill, ended the Royals' four-match winning streak in the tournament. The IPL confirmed the fine, stating that Samson's team maintained a slow over rate during their match.
title: After last-ball drama, Royals captain Samson fined Rs 12 lakh

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi extends warm Eid greetings to Maldives President Mohamed Muizzu, emphasizing cultural ties and values of compassion and togetherness. Eid Al Fitr holds spiritual significance with the traditional moon sighting marking a new month. Despite past challenges, recent efforts show a positive shift in India-Maldives relations.
title: PM Modi extends wishes to Maldives President Muizzu on Eid
Diaspora body urge US govt to address Indian-origin students' deaths

description: Sumit Kumar Singh from Rourkela ran 68.04 km on a manual treadmill in 12 hours, setting a Guinness world record. He aims to promote fitness and mental health awareness, representing India in international races.
title: What happened after a Rourkela man ran 68km on treadmill
Anti-terror operation under way in Pulwama's Frasipora area, Kashmir

description: Muslim leaders caution against false narratives in The Kerala Story, urge vigilance in relationships, and emphasize solidarity with Palestine while protecting democracy through voting.
title: 'Only love, no jihad': Muslim leaders dismiss The Kerala Story as lie

description: Despite efforts to attract more recruiters, older IITs like Bombay and Delhi are facing challenges in placing students. Around 33% of students at IIT Bombay and 40% at IIT Delhi are yet to secure jobs. Undergraduate programs show better results, but master's and PhD programs struggle with lower placement rates.
title: IITs struggle to place students; low paying jobs being rejected

description: All-rounder Rashid Khan's batting secured a thrilling last-ball win for Gujarat Titans against Rajasthan Royals in the 24th match of IPL 2024. Renowned commentator Harsha Bhogle's post-match interaction with GT captain Shubman Gill witnessed a moment of unease, with Bhogle expressing skepticism about the win's timing. Gill's cheeky response, "When GT is playing, don't think (like) that," lightened the atmosphere.
title: Watch: Gill advises Harsha Bhogle to 'not think like that'

description: Rajasthan Royals' skipper Sanju Samson expressed disappointment over their narrow defeat against Gujarat Titans in Jaipur. Despite a valiant effort, RR fell short, as Rashid Khan's heroics secured the victory for GT. Samson found it difficult to articulate his thoughts after the match, stating it was the hardest job in the league.
title: 'The last ball...': Samson on what went wrong for Royals

description: Gujarat Titans defeated Rajasthan Royals in a thrilling Indian Premier League match at Jaipur, thanks to a last-ball finish. Skipper Shubman Gill's half-century set the stage for an exhilarating chase, sealed by Rashid Khan and Rahul Tewatia's heroics. Gill praised Khan's competitiveness and the team's ability to dominate over 50% of the game.
title: 'I would have loved to...': Gill after GT edge RR in last-ball finish

description: The new comprehensive multi-layered, multi-sensor, hi-tech surveillance and intrusion detection systems at the 30 air bases will follow the ongoing installation of a similar integrated perimeter security system (IPSS) at 23 “crucial and sensitive” air bases. “Of the 23 high-priority air bases, the IPSS is now functional at 17-18 after some delay. Now, the plan is to install the IPSS, with some additional features and upgrades, at 30 more air bases,” a senior officer told TOI.
title: 'Smart' multi-layer perimeter security for 30 more IAF bases

description: Ramkishore Shukla's claim of being directed by RSS to switch to Congress before the 2023 elections sparked a political storm in Madhya Pradesh, leading to denials, threats of legal action, and widespread attention on social media.
title: RSS leader sent me to Cong as part of strategy, says 2023 polls candidate

description: China is experiencing a significant resurgence of whooping cough, with cases in the first two months of 2024 soaring more than 20 times compared to the same period in 2023. The National Disease Control and Prevention Administration reported 32,380 cases of pertussis, known as whooping cough, in January and February of 2024, a sharp increase from 1,421 cases during the same timeframe in 2023.
title: With over 12 deaths, whooping cough scare grips China

description: Hardik Pandya's stepbrother, Vaibhav Pandya, arrested for cheating in polymer business partnership, diverting Rs 4.3 crore, breaching profit ratio, and threatening reputation. Capital infusion breach and profit manipulation alleged.
title: Stepbrother held for conning Pandyas of Rs 4cr

description: European companies challenge tech giants like Alphabet, Microsoft, Amazon over cloud bids in the EU. Concerns include data sovereignty, foreign laws, and the impact on EU cloud providers' competitiveness.
title: 18 European firms may have 'bad news' for Google, Microsoft, Amazon

description: The Eid-ul-Fitr is celebrated after a whole month of hard fasting of Ramzan with a reward for all the Muslim devotees to celebrate with their friends and family with delicious dishes and decorations. In this article, we have listed positive messages, wishes, and greetings to share with your loved ones.
title: Eid Mubarak 2024: 50+ happy Eid-ul-Fitr wishes, messages, greetings

description: Manifestos influence policies, from historic Article 370 to present-day reforms. They reflect parties' commitments, shaping India's political landscape. Simplifying complex manifestos and broadening their reach to all languages is essential for inclusive governance. Manifestos are more than political lip service. In fact, reading through a manifesto is like peering through a crystal ball.
title: Why you shouldn’t ignore manifestos

description: Appeals court rejects Trump's delay attempts, hush money trial set to proceed. Legal battles continue over judge rulings, immunity claim, Cohen's payments, and First Amendment rights.
title: Court rejects Donald Trump's third request to delay Monday's hush money trial

description: South Korea's opposition was heading towards a landslide victory in Wednesday's parliamentary elections, exit polls indicated, in a major blow to President Yoon Suk Yeol. However a super majority that would open the door for the opposition to impeach the president looked out of reach as tallies continued into the early morning Thursday.
title: South Korea opposition set for landslide in parliamentary election

description: Vietnamese tycoon Truong My Lan could face death for embezzling $12.5 billion from Saigon Commercial Bank. Amid protests, Lan denies charges of bribery, abuse of power, and causing financial harm. The trial involves 86 accused individuals.
title: Vietnam property tycoon faces verdict in $12.5 billion fraud case

description: Maharashtra Congress president Nana Patole narrowly escaped a truck collision near Bhilewada, sparking a political storm. Congress suspected sabotage, but BJP dismissed conspiracy claims, highlighting the state's political ethos.
title: Cong, BJP trade charges as truck hits Patole's car in Maharashtra

Muslims celebrate with joy, strengthening bonds and reflecting on values like patience and compassion.  For millions of Muslims worldwide, Eid-ul-Fitr 2024 looks to be a time of joy and rebirth.
title: Eid-ul-Fitr 2024: Eid Mubarak Images, Quotes, Wishes, Messages

description: BJP shuffles MPs in UP, bringing Neeraj Shekhar, Sanjay Tandon, and others into the fray. The party strategically places candidates to target specific communities in different constituencies for the upcoming elections.
title: BJP nominates former PM Chandra Shekhar's son for Ballia, SS Ahluwalia for Asansol

description: In the tranquil landscapes of Uttarakhand’s Nainital and Pauri districts, villagers on the fringes of Corbett Tiger Reserve are grappling with the toll of human-animal conflict. In Garhwal (Pauri Garhwal) and Nainital-Udham Singh Nagar, the two LS seats that vote on April 19, one of the biggest issues is big cat-human conflict.
